<h2 id="about-arma-3">About Arma 3</h2>

<div class="vid-container">
  <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/HDJE4-0AK5k" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>
</div>

<p>Arma 3 is one of the top games on Steam by concurrent player count, despite being released years ago. It‚Äôs an open world, military sandbox shooter, that gives you the reigns and allows you to play as you‚Äôd like.</p>

<p>The game allows you to experience true combat gameplay in a massive military open world.</p>

<p>Mods are one of the best things about Arma 3, as they‚Äôre what make the game fresh and playable to this day. Arma 3 has also given birth to many other games, like Player Unknown‚Äôs Battle Grounds, DayZ (and transitively, H1Z1). Arma 3 births other games!</p>

<p>Arma 3 aims to simulate real military combat, and it doe so quite well. Using bullet trajectory simulation, tools like compasses, range finders, and maps, and all of the military devices and vehicles you can think of, and an absolutely massive map, Arma 3 is even used for military training simulations.</p>

<p>Arma 3 is like a kitchen and the modders are cooks, who can turn the game into whatever experience they want. The game can be torn down to its shell and built back up again to become whatever you want.</p>

